<h2>Which One Should You Pick?</h2>

<p>
  Be honest about what you actually share with your partner:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Just a grocery list?</strong> Google Keep or Apple Notes (free, 30 seconds to set up).</li>
  <li><strong>Lists + a shared calendar?</strong> Cupla or Cozi.</li>
  <li><strong>Lists + memories + daily messages?</strong> OurCouple.</li>
  <li><strong>Long-term projects (wedding, trips, finances)?</strong> Notion.</li>
  <li><strong>Tasks and chores?</strong> Any.do or TickTick.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  The right answer depends on whether "shared notes" is a feature you need, or part of a bigger pain (you want a single private space for your relationship). If it's the bigger pain, an all-in-one couples app like <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id6758024356">OurCouple</a> will do better than stitching together Keep + Cozi + Cupla.
</p>

